üõ†Ô∏è Installation and Usage
Prerequisites
Python 3.x installed.
Python libraries: flask (The rest are standard libraries).
Installation
Clone or download this folder.
Install dependencies:
pip install flask feedparser
(Note: feedparser is optional for the solar ticker; the code handles its absence)
Running the App
Launch the main script:
python webapp.py
The engine will start, load the country database (cty.dat), and connect to the clusters.
Open your browser at: http://localhost:8000

üìù Configuration
Open webapp.py to modify:

MY_CALL: Your callsign.
CLUSTERS: The list of Telnet servers.
RARE_PREFIXES: The list of countries YOU consider rare for the score calculation.
